    </div>

    <!-- Photo Book (placeholder structure only for now) -->
    <div id="photo-book" class="mt-10">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold">Photo Book</h2>
      <p class="mt-3 max-w-3xl">
        We‚Äôre creating a friendly picture tour of the house so you can see the rooms, garden and spaces before you visit.
        Photos and captions will be added here soon.
      </p>
    </div>

    <!-- Video tour -->
    <div id="video-tour" class="mt-10">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold">Video Tour</h2>
      <p class="mt-3 max-w-3xl">
        We‚Äôre working on a short, friendly video (about 60‚Äì90 seconds) to show the home, the team and everyday spaces.
        It will be informal, reassuring and include subtitles and a transcript so it‚Äôs easy for everyone to follow.
      </p>

      <div class="mt-4 rounded-2xl border border-dashed p-6 text-center">
        <p class="text-sm text-slate-600">
          Video coming soon. This is where you‚Äôll be able to watch a tour of the home.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Meet the team (child-friendly summary) -->
    <div class="mt-10">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold">Meet the Team</h2>
      <p class="mt-3 max-w-3xl">
        These are some of the grown-ups you might meet. They are here to listen, keep you safe and help you
        feel at home.
      </p>

      <div class="mt-6 grid gap-6 sm:grid-cols-2 md:grid-cols-2">
        <article class="rounded-2xl border p-6">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold">Wikus Cookney</h3>
          <p class="mt-1 text-sm text-slate-600">‚ÄúHi, I‚Äôm Wik. I manage the home.‚Äù</p>
          <p class="mt-3 text-sm">
            I make sure it‚Äôs a safe, warm place. I love fixing things and making sure everyone gets to
            try new activities.
          </p>
        </article>

        <article class="rounded-2xl border p-6">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold">Richard Barfoot</h3>
          <p class="mt-1 text-sm text-slate-600">‚ÄúHi, I‚Äôm Richard. I‚Äôm a mental health nurse.‚Äù</p>
          <p class="mt-3 text-sm">
            I help keep everyone healthy and listened to. I enjoy football and walking in the park.
          </p>
        </article>

        <article class="rounded-2xl border p-6">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold">Siobhan Barfoot</h3>
          <p class="mt-1 text-sm text-slate-600">‚ÄúHi, I‚Äôm Siobhan. I‚Äôm a therapist.‚Äù</p>
          <p class="mt-3 text-sm">
            I help young people with their feelings. I bake cakes at the weekends.
          </p>
        </article>

        <article class="rounded-2xl border p-6">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold">Dr. Hayley Knagg</h3>
          <p class="mt-1 text-sm text-slate-600">‚ÄúHi, I‚Äôm Hayley. I‚Äôm a psychologist.‚Äù</p>
          <p class="mt-3 text-sm">
            I chair our team meetings to make sure plans help you. I like gardening and animals.
          </p>
        </article>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- What to expect -->
    <div class="mt-10">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold">What to Expect</h2>
      <p class="mt-3 max-w-3xl">
        When you move in, we want you to feel welcome, not rushed. Here‚Äôs what will usually happen:
      </p>
      <ul class="mt-3 list-disc pl-6 space-y-2 max-w-3xl">
        <li>You will have a friendly meeting and a little welcome pack.</li>
        <li>We‚Äôll show you around your room and the house.</li>
        <li>You‚Äôll meet your keyworker ‚Äî someone who will listen to you and help make a plan with you.</li>
        <li>We will listen to what you want and help you stay in touch with people who are important to you (if it‚Äôs safe).</li>
        <li>If anything worries you, tell any staff member ‚Äî we‚Äôll help.</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <!-- Family section -->
    <div class="mt-10">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold">Information for Families &amp; Carers</h2>
      <p class="mt-3 max-w-3xl">
        For parents, carers and guardians, we aim to offer clear, practical information and open communication.
      </p>
      <ul class="mt-3 list-disc pl-6 space-y-2 max-w-3xl">
        <li>How we keep children safe, supported and emotionally contained.</li>
        <li>
          A 12-week assessment period including observations, meetings and a co-produced care plan that you are
          invited to contribute to.
        </li>
        <li>Visiting and contact arrangements that are sensitive to each child‚Äôs circumstances and care plan.</li>
        <li>How to request our Statement of Purpose and policies.</li>
        <li>
          Plans for a secure, password-protected area for sensitive photos or reports that should not be shared publicly.
        </li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <!-- Safeguarding & Privacy -->
    <div class="mt-10 rounded-xl bg-[#eef5f4] p-6">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold">Safeguarding &amp; Privacy</h2>
      <p class="mt-3 max-w-3xl">
        Children‚Äôs safety, dignity and privacy come first. We will not publish identifying photos or personal details
        of any child on this public page without explicit written consent from the child (where appropriate), their
        parent or guardian, and the placing authority.
      </p>
      <p class="mt-3 max-w-3xl">
        Photos on this public page will be non-identifying or staged. For family albums showing a child in situ,
        we will use a secure, password-protected area and require written consent.
      </p>
      <p class="mt-3 max-w-3xl">
        Parents and children can withdraw consent at any time, and we will remove images promptly.
        For any requests, please contact:
        <a href="mailto:contact@inguzcare.co.uk" class="underline">contact@inguzcare.co.uk</a>.
      </p>
    </div>

    <!-- Accessibility & inclusion -->
    <div class="mt-10">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold">Accessibility &amp; Inclusion</h2>
      <ul class="mt-3 list-disc pl-6 space-y-2 max-w-3xl">
        <li>All photos will include short alt text.</li>
        <li>Videos will have subtitles and a transcript.</li>
        <li>Text uses plain English with clear headings and easy-to-click buttons.</li>
        <li>
          We can provide a printable A4 version of this information for families who prefer paper or offline access.
        </li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <!-- FAQs -->
    <div class="mt-10">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold">FAQs</h2>
      <div class="mt-4 space-y-4 max-w-3xl">
        <div>
          <p class="font-semibold">Can I bring my things?</p>
          <p class="mt-1">
            Yes ‚Äî we encourage you to bring personal items to make your room feel like yours.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <p class="font-semibold">Can I see the house before I move in?</p>
          <p class="mt-1">
            Yes ‚Äî we can arrange a visit or a video meet so you can see the home and meet some of the team.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <p class="font-semibold">Who can I talk to if I‚Äôm worried?</p>
          <p class="mt-1">
            You can talk to any staff member, your keyworker, or use the ‚ÄúAsk us a question‚Äù option to get in touch.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Contact & feedback -->
    <div class="mt-10 rounded-xl bg-[#eef5f4] p-6">
      <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold">Contact &amp; Feedback</h2>
      <p class="mt-2 max-w-3xl">
        If you would like a private photo album of your child, to talk about consent, or to arrange a visit,
        please get in touch.
      </p>
      <p class="mt-3 max-w-3xl">
        <span class="font-medium">Email:</span>
        <a href="mailto:contact@inguzcare.co.uk" class="underline ml-1">contact@inguzcare.co.uk</a> <br />
        <span class="font-medium">Phone:</span>
        <a href="tel:01619005856" class="underline ml-1">0161 900 5856</a>
      </p>
      <a
        href="/contact"
        class="mt-4 inline-block px-5 py-3 rounded-lg bg-[#5f7c7b] text-white font-semibold hover:bg-[#3d5756]"
      >
        Arrange a visit
      </a>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>
